                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-04-06T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1926—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>77. Your 131, March 16, 10 A.M. Department prefers to take no action in matter in
                    the absence of a request from interested firm. In this connection see
                    Department’s telegram No. 298 of November 17, 6 p.m. 1921.<note n="95"
                        xml:id="d848fn95">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
